        "discriminators": [
          "DESIGNED vs REAL is a PRODUCTION distinction, not an acoustic one — it is the same detonation morphology either way — so this is semantic_only however it is dressed up.",
          "The tendencies are real but soft, and are PRIORS, never gates: a designed explosion is usually LONGER, carries a deliberately exaggerated sub-100 Hz layer, has an engineered tail, and is WIDE in stereo because it was mixed rather than captured on a single mic. A field recording of real ordnance is narrower, shorter and less sub-heavy.",
          "No gate can honestly separate this from EXPLOSIONS-REAL. Text decides; where text is silent, prefer EXPLOSIONS-MISC over guessing."
        ],
