        "discriminators": [
          "A detonation: broadband, violently front-loaded, LF-dominated, with a long decaying tail as the shockwave slaps off the terrain. It is a BURST, not a clean impulse — the front is loud and fast but not the single needle-sharp transient of a whip crack.",
          "Against DESTRUCTION-COLLAPSE and DESTRUCTION-CRASH & DEBRIS, and this is the boundary worth trusting: an explosion is ONE event with its energy in the first moment (envelope_temporal_centroid LOW, few discrete onsets afterwards). Destruction is MANY events spread across the file (high transient_count, energy spread out). That comparison is genuinely measurable.",
          "Against GUNS-ARTILLERY / GUNS-CANNON: acoustically the same event — a cannon report IS a detonation. Only text decides.",
          "Against FIREWORKS-COMMERCIAL: a mortar is an explosion, usually with a launch thump before it and a crackle train after it. If a multi-onset crackle tail is present, prefer FIREWORKS.",
          "Against EXPLOSIONS-DESIGNED: not decidable. See that entry."
        ],
